OL,3,CRail users face 'don't travel' message
OL,4,Cafter axing of HS2 watchdog warns
OL,6,FThe Office says that given that HS2
OL,7,FLtd, the government-owned company
OL,8,Fbehind the project, estimates there
OL,9,Fwill be a 17% reduction in capacity
OL,10,Fbetween the two cities, and that the
OL,11,FDepartment for Transport believes the
OL,12,FWCML will reach capacity by the mid-
OL,13,F2030's, the Department may need to
OL,14,F'manage demand'.
OL,16,FThis could include "incentivising
OL,17,Fpeople to travel at different times or
OL,18,Fto not travel by rail".
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/11
